For each month during the term of this Agreement, HPS will pay to SHPS an amount equal to (i) eighty-two and one-half percent (82.5%) of the first $500,000 of Care Management Revenues (as defined below) during such month plus (ii) eighty percent (80%) of Care Management Revenues during such month in excess of $500,000. modified:
2. PAYMENTS 2.1 FEES FOR CURRENT SHPS CLIENTS. For each calendar month during the term of this Agreement, SHPS will receive from HPS an amount equal to (i) 17.5% of the first $500,000 of Care Management Fees (as defined below) for that month, plus (ii) 20% of any Care Management Fees exceeding $500,000 for that same period. HPS will make this payment to SHPS within thirty days following the end of the relevant calendar month. At the time of payment, HPS shall provide SHPS with a schedule detailing the calculation of fees payable under this Section 2.1 and Care Management Fees per Client for the respective month.

In this revised clause, the obligation on HPS to make payments has been weakened by reducing the percentage rate paid to SHPS for both the initial $500,000 and any excess amounts, as well as extending the payment deadline from fifteen to thirty days following the end of the month. Furthermore, the responsibility for providing the schedule detailing the calculation of fees has been shifted to HPS.

original: 4.9  WAIVER. No delay or omission by either party to exercise any right or power in this Agreement shall impair such right or power or be construed to be a waiver of such right or power. A waiver by either of the parties shall not be construed to be a waiver of any succeeding breach or of any other covenant contained in this Agreement.

4.9 WAIVER AND CONSTRUCTION. Any forbearance or failure to enforce by either party any provision of this Agreement shall not be deemed a waiver of the right to do so regarding subsequent occurrences, nor shall it affect the validity of this Agreement as a whole. A waiver on one occasion does not necessarily constitute a waiver of similar rights or obligations in the future.

Changes made:
1. Replaced "No delay or omission" with "Any forbearance or failure to enforce" (subtlety changes the tone slightly and makes it less abrupt)
2. Changed "shall impair" to "shall not be deemed a waiver of" (weakening the obligation by stating that it is not necessarily the case, but rather a possibility)
3. Changed "A waiver by either of the parties shall not be construed to be a waiver" to "A waiver on one occasion does not necessarily constitute a waiver" (rephrased for clarity and to emphasize that future occurrences are not guaranteed)
4. Added "of similar rights or obligations in the future" (to further weaken the obligation by explicitly stating that a waiver may only apply to similar rights or obligations, not all covenants contained in the Agreement)
